<item>
            <title>[JDK-8308997] RISC-V: Sign extend when comparing 32-bit value with zero instead of testing the sign bit</title>
                <link>https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8308997</link>
                <project id="10100" key="JDK">JDK</project>
                    <description>RISC-V branch and jump instructions use 64-bit registers instead of 32-bit &lt;br/&gt;
versions in RV64I. We use test_bit to test if bit 31 is zero to determine if a&lt;br/&gt;
32-bit register is less than zero currently.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
However, there will be two instructions when we use test_bit to test bit&lt;br/&gt;
31/63 without Zbs extension[1], we can just use sign_extend instead, which&lt;br/&gt;
only use one instruction.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
At the same time, we also change some 32-bit symbolic extension operations to&lt;br/&gt;
sign_extend for better readability.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
[1] &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/openjdk/jdk/blob/e21f865d84c7c861843ff568019e1ad11d280a50/src/hotspot/cpu/riscv/macroAssembler_riscv.cpp#L4596-L4603&quot;&gt;https://github.com/openjdk/jdk/blob/e21f865d84c7c861843ff568019e1ad11d280a50/src/hotspot/cpu/riscv/macroAssembler_riscv.cpp#L4596-L4603&lt;/a&gt;</description>
